acceptance_criteria: "A first-party baseline/profile package is installable; it uses public SDK APIs only; package catalog/describe/doctor are clean; docs and examples explain the archetype; SDK testing helpers cover registrations; temp-project dogfood installs the package, applies the profile, and creates sample items."
parent: pm-ugqx
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-v37g,blocked_by,"2026-06-25T06:44:15.434Z",claude-code-agent,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T04:57:08.891Z",codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625,"Duplicate check: status-all package/profile searches found closed package platform and exemplar work, while pm package catalog currently has no baseline/profile/archetype package."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T07:28:54.194Z",claude-code-agent,"ENABLING PRIMITIVE SHIPPED (in the pm-v37g/pm-bhmk profiles PR): SDK now exports defineProjectProfile (typed identity builder for ProjectProfileDefinition), BUILTIN_PROFILES, PROFILE_NAMES, resolveProfile, listProfiles, normalizeProfileName, and the pure planProfileApplication + ProfileApplicationPlan/ProfileCurrentState types. The three built-in archetypes (agile/ops/research) dogfood the model. REMAINING follow-up scope for this item: build an installable first-party package (e.g. pm-baseline-profile) that defines a profile via defineProjectProfile AND make it applicable from a package. Gap: profile apply orchestration (lock/write/hooks/templates) lives in cli/commands/profile.ts and is NOT yet SDK-exported, and `pm profile apply` only resolves BUILTIN_PROFILES — there is no external-profile registration path yet. So pm-a7o4 needs either (a) an SDK applyProfile orchestration export + an extension capability to register profiles into the `pm profile` resolver, or (b) the package ships a thin command that calls planProfileApplication + writes. Keep open, blocked-by pm-v37g (now satisfied for the primitive half)."
body: ""
